Remove stalk and core from the @red pepper{1} and @yellow pepper{1/2}(cut into thin slices). Peel and finely dice the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and finely diced). Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{3}(finely chopped). Cut the @cherry tomatoes{1}(cut in half) in half. Chop the @British chicken thighs{2} into bite-sized chunks. Boil @water{300%ml} with the @chicken stock pot{1} in a #pot{}.

Set #hob{} to high heat and heat @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a #frying pan{}. Season the chicken well with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Add the chicken to the frying pan and fry for a few minutes. Once it is brown on all sides, remove and keep to the side.

Add another @olive oil{2%tbsp} into the frying pan. Add the peppers and cherry tomatoes. Cook for a few minutes until they've softened up. Add in the garlic, @rosemary{1%tsp}(leaves only) and the @diced chorizo{1/3}.

After ~{3%minutes}, add half the parsley and the @basmati rice{1}. Cook for a few minutes until the rice absorbs the oil.

Add the chicken stock and chicken. Give everything a good stir. Reduce heat to medium-low and cook for ~{15-20%minutes}.

> Tip: Don't stir - a good paella always has a crusty bottom!

Once the liquid has soaked up, take the paella off the heat. Cover with a clean #tea towel{} and leave for ~{5%minutes}. Serve with the remaining parsley and big wedges of @lemon{1/2}(cut into wedges).